  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Lay</strong> the cucumber flat on your chopping board and use a rolling pin to bash it so that it splits and breaks up (some force is required)</p>\r\n<p>Tip: Wear an apron as the juices will splatter!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cut</strong> the broken cucumber into rough bite-size pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> and finely chop (or grate) the garlic</p>\r\n<p><strong>Toss</strong> the cucumber with 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(1 tsp)</span> salt and the chopped garlic in a sieve and set aside over a bowl</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Peel</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop the ginger</p>\r\n<p><strong>Slice</strong> the chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">(es)</span> in half lengthways, scrape the seeds out (with a teaspoon) and chop ﬁnely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Combine</strong> the ginger, chilli, rice wine vinegar and soy sauce with 1 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(3 tbsp)</span> sugar and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tbsp)</span> vegetable oil</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the noodles to a pot of salted boiling water over a high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Boil</strong> for 4-6 min until cooked through but with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, chop the spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span>, discarding the root ends</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> cooked, drain and return them to the pan off the heat</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, pat the steaks dry with kitchen towel and then rub with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tsp)</span> vegetable oil and season generously with salt</p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat</strong> a wide-based, dry pan (preferably non-stick) on a high heat and once hot, cook the steaks on each side for 1 min</p>\r\n<p><strong>Transfer</strong> the cooked steaks to a clean board, cover with a tea towel and rest for 5 min, reserving the pan</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Return</strong> the pan to a low heat (leave it to cool slightly if it's very hot)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the ginger chilli sauce and cook for 1 min or until starting to bubble and caramelise</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> bubbling, tip the noodles in and mix well to coat them in the sauce, then remove from the heat</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/414.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
